column10: dig_threshold_desc:I started using this strategy from the beginning
column11: but in an uneducated way at first. But as I worked out some basic estimations of the gems per unit time of digs and compared it to the \base rate\ of ~105 gems / 15 seconds of travel time (dig to dig)
column12: I decided to always leave when the number of gems got between 24 and 32.
column16: dynamic_desc:In the beginning I used this a little. I tried to think of the probability of getting a good planet vs. a bad planet and gave up quickly when the gem haul dropped tremendously after the first dig.
column19: I settled on a strategy of keeping the overall
column20: amortized gem/second rate above the \base rate\ baked in by the roughly 105 gems (avg.) per 15 seconds of dig-to-dig travel time (or thereabouts). That works out to about 7-8 gems per second. To ensure I never fell below this (where it would then make sense to give up and travel)
column21: I stopped digging when I hit 24-32 gems. With each dig taking about 3-4 seconds
column23: feedback:I'm sure there are some equations that could be solved to maximize the amount of gems per second
column24: but I couldn't do all that in my head.}
